<TITLE> France's Sarkozy separates from wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, Oct 18, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - French President Nicolas Sarkozy and his wife Cecilia are separating by mutual agreement, the president's office said in a statement on Thursday. The announcement ends weeks of speculation about the state of the Sarkozy marriage and follows media reports that the pair secretly saw a judge on Monday to file for divorce. Cecilia played no public part in her husband's election campaign this year, did not vote for him at the second round ballot and only appeared alongside him at three public engagements since his May victory -- the last time in July. Sarkozy, 52, and Cecilia, a 49-year old former model, got married in 1996 and have a 10-year old son together. They briefly separated in 2005, but got back together in a blaze of publicity at the start of last ye
